How does the SUSE solution help them (required): No current management plane for WindRiver/OpenStack environment. Team had to build and manage all today. Give them management plane and so much more with Rancher Suite. They can get entire off WR platform and move everything to us
Relevant history / background on the account (required): Dish has been a long time SUSE customer. Boost is a new division we just started working with
Use Case / Applications: Manage NTP, Firewall and DNS. Potential parts of the core network down the line
What operating system / infrastructure (hardware, cloud, etc) are they currently running:
Is MEDDPICC completed if over $100k+ potential ACV? Complete the free form fields that are relevant (Scorecard drop-down is optional)
Dependency (Roadblock) to make it happen: Current WindRiver contract, couldn&#39;t get out of agreement and have 4 years left. Additional contract disputes with tower providers since Dish sold spectrum to AT&amp;T. Working to complete MSA
Compelling Event: Pricing for other DISH divisions expires 4/30/26. Trying to co-term and give DISH all you can eat agreement
Agreed upon Mutual Go Live plan: No, working to create

2/16 - Sarah sent over EULA and Subcription terms. Waiting to receive initial documents for review of MSA

2/12 - Met with Dean/Mitch from Dish. Started process for MSA. Will receive initial documents early next week

1/27 - Pushing to Q2. Working to finalize MSA ASAP. Waiting for Reorg to complete for new counts and structure of deal

1/21 - working to finalize VLA acceptance document with old Rancher Agreement per easiest path with customer. Customer has quote

1/13 - WindRiver contract is finalized. Met with Nate, got confirmation and plan to move forward. revising quote and scheduled meeting w/ Legal &amp; Procurement for 1/15

12/11 - Need to finalize VLA Acceptance document. DISH is finalizing getting out of the Wind River contract which is taking precedence for us getting anything completed

10/22 - The quote is in our final procurement process, we&#39;re finalizing legal sign-off and executive leadership sign-off. However, that being said we are fully commercially aligned and expecting closure before EOM.

10/16 - Sent revised updated 1yr quote. Dish is committed to getting PO by EOM

10/13 - Sent revised pricing, new quote is in Dish hands. Waiting for update and follow-up from their internal meeting

10/1 - Building our SUSE Telco Suite bundle for Dish. Presenting 3yr pricing for Suite, PSE Gold, Consulting and training

Dish sold off a large portion of Boost to AT&amp;T, which involved a large portion of their Wind River and VMware estate. They need a new solution moving forward for K8s and virtualization. They have chosen to use Rancher and SUSE Virt</td><td align=right>10/1/2025</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@"></td></tr>
