- Tanner to have a pre-sales resource ready to assist Pellera w/ me today to review their SUSE proposal
- In prep for this afternoon, Pellera has asked for SUSE Sales to
- -- find out how SUSE supports LDAP in SLES or MLS....the RH support for LDAP is an add on called &quot;Directory Server&quot;
- -- proactively obtain SKUs for extreme LTSS for MLS for RHEL 5, 6, (and 7 if needed)

Notes
- Openshift OVE + RH / Advanced cluster manager
- RHEL lite ESP / MSRP $330K / unlimited RHEL (price per server $350)
- 412 Linux VMs
- Directory Server = 389 Directory Server  / so that you can have LDAP

10/07  TM - Call with Pellera and Saul.  Talked about MLS and MLM.  They are also going to pursue virtualization as a replacement for VMware.  Next step is to scope out the entire enviroment and help Saul put a proposal together for his boss.  The goal is to replace RH and have a viable option to replace VMware.

10/07 JR - John (Pellera rep) set a call for today at 1 w/ the customer. Pricing was shared and customer found price favorable. Customer renewed Openshift in Sept for 1 year and is looking at SUSE as an alternative as they are not happy with IBM/RH pricing and practices. 

For today&#39;s call Pellera will talk about a migration plan and how once they start work that SUSE Rancher support should be purchased for initial environments. Also looking to understand what the RHEL estate looks like (counts, versions, renewal data), and when they would start migration and start support.
 
10/6  TM  Quotes were created and sent to Mainline.
10/01 JR - Asked Peller contact (SA Josh Minthorne) if he could set up a call w/ the rep on the 2nd or 6th since no meet was set for today. 

9/26/25 JR - Josh Minthorne (SA) called me to discuss opportunity. Pellera is helping customer replace VMware for hypervisor and Kubernetes. Will be a baremetal 3 year Rancher Prime Suite SKU. Possilbe MLS to be added. Josh is working on persenting budgetary pricing with the Perella AE and will determine when RH renewal is and determine if this can be pulled forward.</td><td align=right>9/26/2025</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Cloud Native</td></tr>
