10/01/25 JR - they are being forced by vendor management and leadership to look at RedHat OVE due to price point. So we are losing shot at closing FY25. Technologent meeting the customer team on afternoon of Oct 6th to go over the entire solution stack and re assess SUSE standing (SUSE&#39;s SKU core limit compared to RH is pricing SUSE out).

9/12 JR - Technologent update today. Customer pivot on strategy. Will renew VMware for 1 year CQ1 2026, also executing on a mandate to immediately select a challenger to VMware. Director level wants SUSE, practitioner wants OVM. Technologent motivated to close in Oct. Will get update on progress with October close w/in 10 days.

8/25 JR - feedback on pricing via Technologent...Wanted to let you know we had a follow-on conversation this morning with Cooley with the updated pricing and the larger customer team.  They were appreciative of our proposal and adjusted pricing; however, they do not feel that the discounted pricing is enough of a savings against VMWARE that they would risk the migration from VMWARE to Rancher.  He did state if we can get exceptionally more aggressive on a three-year price, he would be willing to listen to us further. Customer also stated on the call this would most likely be a Q2 or Q3 2026 Opportunity. 

8/22 - VMware renewal in Feb. Customer planning decision between VCF and Rancher in October/Nov and for Technologent to start planning migration. Technologent to attempted to close some in Q4 but funds are not available until Jan. Vendor selection in Sept.

8/14 JR - Cooley has a VMware renewal Q1 26 and is seeking alternatives. RH, SUSE, and Vmware are in the mix. Cooley runs a small number of K8s apps. biggest challenge to win is Vmware is priced lower than SUSE (both VVF and VCF) and there will be significant migration effort to get off VMware.</td><td align=right>7/24/2025</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Cloud Native</td></tr>
