DR: There are numerous different flavors of Linux subscriptions at NRG through numerous acquisitions, etc.  We are specifically working on trying to convince NRG to combine all their Redhat to SUSE using MLS because they would save a tremendoes amount of money.

July 22 - JR - Working w/ Emma to level set on how we support David and Tony


High Level Overview of Opportunity- Renewal is in Dec, Technologent put in deal red, but the normally go with Mark III 
Which SUSE sales play does this opportunity focus on?- MLS 
Virtualization or MLS? - MLS 
Is this a new opportunity or upsell?- net new 
Use Case / Applications?- RH take out, put more money towards Rancher 
What operating system are they currently running?- RH 
Have we tried to sell services?- no, but will 
Partners involved?- Technologent or Mark III 
Cloud vendor?- GCP
MEDDPICC completed if over $100k ACV - not yet need counts 
Compelling event? Why now?- Start saving money on linux and put it towards cloud native 
Do we have IBM / Red Hat quantities and expiration date?- Dec need counts 
Do we have Broadcom / VMWare expiration date? - no

