<tr><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Insight Direct USA Inc</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">0</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Michaels (T)</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Michaels - SUSE Edge Core - Phase 2</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">OP00491069</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Andrew Carlsen</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Upside</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Q4-2026</td><td align=right>10/16/2026</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">NAM NASA</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>334600.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>334600.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>0.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">AC 12/13/25: Set meeting with In-Store systems team and Infrastructure team to discuss support options.</td><td>AC 12/11/25: In-Store systems team and Infrastructure team have reached out asking for meeting to discuss pricing for Rancher, as they currently are assessing Rancher as a viable option for managing the Fleet in our Store Environment. They want to explore support plans and services as well. Insight has emerged as a potential reseller, and Lenovo has emerged as the hardware vendor. 



JR 8/27/2025: Presidio has relationships at Michaels / Security and Network // Introduced Presidio team to SUSE team // Presidio to leverage relationships and resources to engage customer at a higher level so that we ca jointly speak to our joint value in bringing outcomes based on what SUSE has learned so far on this opp / Andrew and Thomas from Presidio to stay connected on updates and progress

AC 8/20/25: Meeting with In-Store systems team to gain an idea if their value/wants/needs. Looking to gain executive buy in from Decision Maker(s) Suresh S - VP of Infra, and Wei Dong - CISO. Need buy in from Store Systems team, and from the CISO.
AC 8/8/25: Michaels has replied for a follow up meeting to discuss pricing for week of 8/8. Will confirm proposal slides with Mark Abrams, and present pricing and vision for 5 year plan.
AC 6/3/25: Dheeraj requested 5 year pricing info for SUSE Edge: SLE micro &amp; Rancher. Will set call and loop in Mark Abrams to address questions from our side. We will want to understand roll out (1st year, 2nd year etc) and timeline.
AC 5/16/25: Edge Deep-dive call set for 5/22, Oleg from SUSE will lead. Dheeraj &amp; Niraj from Michaels attending along with others relevant to project.

AC 4/24/25: Follow up demo/hands on call with Dheeraj and team. In development phase now, will workshop POC, pilot phase in August, business roll out Q4/25 or Q1/26..

AC 4/22/25: Meeting set with Dheeraj for 4/24 for follow up. 

1.Michaels is exploring containerization solutions for their 1,400 isolated store systems, with a focus on centralized management and troubleshooting.
2.Rancher and Portainer are the solutions they are currently evaluating, with Rancher already in use for logging purposes.
3.Michaels is looking to implement the new containerized solution by Q3 this year, as it is a strategic initiative for the company.
4.Michaels is primarily using Debian-based Linux, but is open to evaluating SUSE solutions as well.
5.Michaels is interested in exploring AI capabilities, but does not have any current initiatives in this area.


Close Plan:
Priority is executive alignment. We have proposed budgetary pricing to our main contact, Niraj Gupta, who is Dr. of Infrastructure Engineering. His management and VP, Suresh S. will be key approvers, along with the Store Systems Engineering team. This will go up to the CISO, and to the economic buyer - the CIO - Uma Bhemsetty. 

Partner/VAR: Michaels has not disclosed, either open to our expertise or they will decide based on value-add.

Next Steps continued: We will need buy in from VP of Infra, Store Systems team, CISO and sign off from CIO. I set a call with store systems team, from there I will look to get connected with the Dr. of Cybersecurity, and the CISO.
Scott J. will connect with Suresh S. (vp of infra) to have alignment there. Looking to have this alignment solidified by end of week of 8/18. 

POC, PTAS and Pilot into roll-out are our goal for Q4, as the compelling event is busy holiday season after Oct.</td><td align=right>4/16/2025</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@"></td></tr>
