<tr><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Presidio Networked Solutions INC</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">0</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Walt Disney Co (The) (T)</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">DCL - Rancher - Presidio - Joel/Hunter - RenewalOpp: 00143251 - 2026-04-01 - 2027-03-31 (291954.60USD, origin 12M)</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">OP00489560</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Joel Millares</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Commit</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Q2-2026</td><td align=right>3/31/2026</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">NAM West Strategic</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>699480.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>407525.40</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>291954.60</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">3/5 (JM) - ELA meeting set for 3/5 with Disney Sourcing, SUSE Legal and Zac to discuss final parameters.</td><td>What is the customer trying to achieve (required):  Rancher Prime renewal plus growth for DCL&#39;s ships and private islands.  Subscription conversion from node to vCPU.  One of business unit opportunities helping drive urgency for ELA with Sourcing.

How does the SUSE solution help them (required):  Their cruise ships are DataCenters on water with sometimes limited connectivity.  Their goal is to run everything which does not require Windows or a standalone VM on Kubernetes. Rancher allows for simplified management of the Kubernetes infrastructure by Non-dedicated Ship IT officers.  

Relevant history / background on the account (required):  Long-term Rancher customer that has continued to grow their footprint with the addition of new cruise ships.  They have had CSAT issues in the past due to the RKE to RKE2 re-platforming and there is constant pressure from leadership to move to EKS.  Due to their over-provisioning of CPU while on the node pricing model, the move to vCPU pricing is causing a lot of pain from a budgetary standpoint to where it could force them to seek an alternative to Rancher.

Use Case / Applications:  The SUSE Solution is Cloud Native Container Management.  Each Cruise ship and Private Island is a separate data center with limited connectivity.  So each Ship and Island has it&#39;s own Rancher Management Cluster with 4 -5 application clusters.  The Applications are all custom build by Disney and include Guest Embarkation, Backend POS, Vacation planner for Guests and, most websites etc. Rancher lets them be agnostic of where these workloads are.

What operating system / infrastructure (hardware, cloud, etc) are they currently running:  The Ship and Island infrastructure is VMWare delivering the Kubernetes Nodes.  The OS Is Ubuntu for all of the RKE2 Kubernetes nodes.  Disney does run some workloads in AWS for Dev, Test and QA environments.

Is MEDDPICC completed if over $100k+ potential ACV? Complete the free form fields that are relevant (Scorecard drop-down is optional):  Yes

Dependency (Roadblock) to make it happen:  Pricing and ELA with ability to buy direct

Compelling Event: Yes, support contract ends 3/31

Agreed upon Mutual Go Live plan:</td><td align=right>4/1/2025</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@"></td></tr>
