<tr><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Presidio Networked Solutions INC</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">0</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Walt Disney Co (The) (T)</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">DSS - MLM Pilot - Evotek/Dell - Existing - Joel/Hunter</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">OP00484374</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Joel Millares</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Upside</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Q3-2026</td><td align=right>6/26/2026</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">NAM West Strategic</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>150000.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>150000.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>0.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">3/5 (JM) - Matt has been caught up in an urgent priority work stream which has slowed our mutual process.  Moving this opp to Q3 for time being and will meet with Matt in NYC on 3/19 during Streaming QBR.</td><td>What is the customer trying to achieve (required): MLM pilot for 2000 systems as a test case for patching 20k-30k systems at full scale for inherited HULU systems and then moving to support all new systems.

How does the SUSE solution help them (required): With less than a year to build a patching solution that works with their overarching automation project, MLM provides a turnkey solution to manage their infrastructure and patch their 20-30k systems.  A single security vulnerability in their custom code, a key engineer leaving, or a major change in OS patching methodologies could cripple their operations. Compliance audits become a significant manual burden.  MLM becomes a critical part of their larger systems management solution, where they will add CMDB, System Owner level management, Approval flows for automated Change Control to name just a few.

Relevant history / background on the account (required): Streaming has been a legacy Rancher customer for many years.  This opp was uncovered last year at a QBR where the infrastructure team attended and advised of a need for a patching solution.

Use Case / Applications:  The primary use case is the Patch Curation and Management functions.  There are really no other Open Source or COTS applications that have the ability to provide this capability for multiple Linux Distros in a cost effective way.  With the API capabilites MLM can effectively be the central Patch and compliance soltuion component while allowing the Disney team to add CMDB, Approval workflows, System Deployment Automation, System Owner management capabilities as they have time to build those additional features.  

What operating system / infrastructure (hardware, cloud, etc) are they currently running: Ubuntu for the bulk of the systems that are currently being patched effectively.  There are also some RHEL systems to be managed.  All of the 20,000 to 30,000 systems are on prem in 4 data centers.  There are additional systems spread across the world to support the additional streaming capabilities.  There is all of the major hardware vendors represented, but the majority are White Box Clones.

Is MEDDPICC completed if over $100k+ potential ACV? Complete the free form fields that are relevant (Scorecard drop-down is optional): Yes

Dependency (Roadblock) to make it happen: EB has a build vs. buy strategy preference and original budget had been re-allocated during a major re-org last year.

Compelling Event: Yes, ESPN/Streaming has the Super Bowl in 2027 and their automation and patching need to be clean and in order ahead of the Super Bowl.

Agreed upon Mutual Go Live plan: Yes</td><td align=right>2/14/2025</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@"></td></tr>
