<tr><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Technologent</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">1</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">PNC Financial Services Group Inc (T)</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">PNC-Rancher-Reseller-NNN-Baynard/Bryce</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">OP00468531</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Matthew Baynard</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Pipeline</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Q3-2026</td><td align=right>5/22/2026</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">NAM East Strategic</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>549000.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>549000.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>0.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">2/23 - Matt, Joe and Abraham on next steps and project detail status and how we can move it forward</td><td>DR

This opportunity started as an RFP several months ago. Suse had to bow out of the Response because we could not come to agreement on the non-disclosure agreement with PNC.  David was able to get us through the NDA after request from PNC to resubmit an offer. Legal was instrumental and bailing us out of this issue and we were able to come to agreement with PNC on the NDA.  

We have been working closely with Technologent on this opportunity and Abraham has been instrumental and working with senior leader ship inside PNC outside of the RFP response. It has been an all hands on deck Response with Jeff Lindholm, Anthony, Justin, and several others in getting their response back to them since while others had six weeks to respond Susa basically had five days.

PNC had been testing Tazo to which was a major disaster and had actually purchased open shift. Open shift has proven to be problematic for them and they basically stopped for deployment other than a small development group for in-house applications. PNC has been looking for a solution that does not tie them to a vendor and is also very portable when it comes to containers.  We did not know at the time, but PNC had been doing some skunk work testing with Rancher and really liked what they saw. They had attended several Rancher web sessions in the last six months. At this point, we are waiting for formal responses from PNC on the RFP, however, in the background, Technologent has been working with several executives pushing Rancher and they feel very strongly that they have a significant leg up on any possible solution from the other RFP respondents.

Opp: OpenShift alternative and modernization acceleration
Description: Customer looking for alternative container platforms as price increases and difficulty onboarding apps with current platform has become a problem for the business. There is a strong desire to accelerate adoption of Kubernetes and investment in cloud native tools. Technologent is working with the customer on alternative solutions and Rancher has been shown the them and is a viable alternative. Technologent will be working with customer on a platform migration plan as well as a plan to accelerate Kubernetes adoption. Customer has also identified AzureStack and AKS and a possible alternative.</td><td align=right>9/19/2024</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@"></td></tr>
<tr><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Presidio Networked Solutions INC</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">0</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center (T)</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Memorial Sloan- Rancher  New Biz</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">OP00455847</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Bart Nicolay</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Upside</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">Q3-2026</td><td align=right>6/19/2026</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">NAM East Enterprise</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>242200.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>242200.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">USD</td><td align=right>0.00</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@">BN 10/31:  Project paused but expected to resume before EOY.  Finally aligned with key partner Converge/Pellera, Mike Verola,  with long history in the account.  Targeting on-site meeting in early December.</td><td>Use Case: Migration from Tanzu &amp; OpenShift 

Key Contacts: 

Mariano D&#39;Angelo: Lead Infrastructure Architect

Edward Olenelu: Senior Mgr- Virtualization

500 nodes. Customer renewed 3 YR deal with Tanzu in October but has since been mandated to move off on Tanzu before next renewal. POC to kick off in Q2 and finish by Q3 with decision made by end of Q3. Migrations to begin in Q4 is selected. Competitor is Nutanix. 

LL 7/30: Scheduling meeting second week of August as team is on vacation right now. Meeting to focus around transition from Tanzu to Rancher

LL 12/10: Second meeting scheduled with MSKCC on Dec 17th. Looking to position Rancher Suite and firm up timeline/migration path

LL 12/20: Meeting with MSKCC on 1/6

LL 1/6: Second meeting had with MSKCC today. Use case to move away from Tanzu. Whiteboarded their processes of provisioning under current set up with Tanzu/TMC. Next steps meeting on the 24th for MSKCC to present architectural overview and processes.

LL 2/3: Onsite scheduled for Feb 11 to discuss/present solution overview of Tanzu-&gt;Rancher, as well as SUSE Virtualization to replace current hypervisor</td><td align=right>6/11/2024</td><td style="vnd.ms-excel.numberformat:@"></td></tr>
